🔹 1. SSL/TLS (Secure Communication)
------------------------------
 - Secure communication between client & server
 
 SSL → Old (deprecated)
 TLS → Modern (used now)

 Used in:
 - HTTPS
 - APIs
 - Web apps

 Example:
 http://site.com  → Not secure
 https://site.com → Secure

 TLS Flow:
 Client → Hello
 Server → Certificate
 Client → Verify
 → Encrypted communication starts

 Features:
 - Encryption → Data hidden
 - Integrity → No tampering
 - Authentication → Verify server


🔹 2. IPSec (Network Security)
------------------------------
 - Secures communication at network level

 Used in:
 - VPN
 - Site-to-site connection
 - Cloud networking

 Modes:
 Transport Mode → Encrypts data only
 Tunnel Mode → Encrypts entire packet

 Difference:
 TLS → Secure message
 IPSec → Secure network


🔹 3. DevSecOps
------------------------------
 DevSecOps = Dev + Security + Ops

 Goal:
 - Fast delivery
 - Secure systems
 - Automation

 Pipeline:
 Code → Build → Test → Scan → Deploy → Monitor


🔹 4. DevSecOps Tools
------------------------------

 SAST (Static Testing)
 - Scan code before execution
 Tools:
 - SonarQube
 - Checkmarx

 DAST (Dynamic Testing)
 - Test running apps
 Tools:
 - Burp Suite

 SCA (Dependency Scan)
 - Check libraries
 Tools:
 - Snyk
 - Dependabot

 Container Security
 - Scan Docker images
 Tools:
 - Trivy
 - Clair

 Secrets Management
 - Store credentials securely
 Tools:
 - HashiCorp Vault
 - AWS Secrets Manager


🔹 5. Shell Scripting
------------------------------
 - Automating Linux commands

 Shell:
 - Program that executes commands

 Types:
 - Bash (most used)
 - sh
 - zsh


🔹 6. Basic Script
------------------------------
 #!/bin/bash
 echo "Hello World"

 Commands:
 chmod +x script.sh
./script.sh


🔹 7. Shell Types
------------------------------
 sh → Basic shell
 bash → Advanced shell

 Bash Features:
 - Variables
 - Loops
