 - Auto-completion


🔹 8. Variables
------------------------------
 - Store data

 Syntax:
 name="value"

 Example:
 name="Niranjana"
 echo $name


🔹 9. Types of Variables
------------------------------

 1. User-defined
 - Created by user
 - Local scope

 2. System variables
 - Predefined by OS
 Examples:
 $HOME, $USER, $PWD, $SHELL

 3. Environment variables
 - Global scope
 - Accessible by child processes

 Set:
 export MY_VAR="Hello"

 Check:
 env


🔹 10. Variable Behavior
------------------------------
 User Variable:
 - Local
 - NOT inherited by child process

 Environment Variable:
 - Global
 - Inherited by child process


🔹 11. Make Variable Persistent
------------------------------
 Temporary:
 export MY_VAR="Hello"

 Permanent:
 Add in ~/.bashrc

 System-wide:
 sudo nano /etc/environment
